## Poll

Conceptually similar to base post (content with time limit, no publication `metrics.score`). In code, **Poll is a separate entity**: its own collection (`polls`) and schema with `question`, `options`, `expiresAt`, and metrics (`totalCasts`, `casterCount`, `totalAmount`). Voting is via **`polls.cast`** / **`poll_casts`** (merit-weighted choice per option), not publication **`Vote`** rows. It is not a Publication subtype or a publication with `postType: 'poll'`.

### Differences from Base Post

| Characteristic | Base Post | Poll |
|----------------|-----------|------|
| Own rating (`metrics.score`) | Yes | No (poll has its own metrics on the Poll document) |
| Merit-weighted feedback | `Vote` on publication (`votes.*`) | `polls.cast` (option choice; not a publication Vote) |
| Additional fields | — | Question, answer options |
| Time limit | No | Optional (`expiresAt`) |

### Poll-Specific Fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| question | Poll question text |
| options | List of voting options |
| expiresAt | Voting close time (required in schema) |

### Poll Voting
- Poll creation uses `settings.pollCost` (community-level cost)
- Poll voting spends user merits by vote amount (wallet/quota rules apply)
- Vote weight = amount of merits spent
- After expiresAt, new votes are NOT accepted

